## Real-World Use Case

Imagine an e-commerce company launching a new Inventory Management application.

Before developers can deploy the application, the DevOps team must:

* Provision a database server
* Create a dedicated application database
* Generate secure database credentials
* Grant only the permissions required for that application
* Deliver the connection details to the development team

This separation ensures multiple applications can safely share the same database server without interfering with one another.

